caption: Absolutely amazing :) wonderful cheese & charcuterie selections. Service was top notch

My wife and I visited Duck Duck Goose this past weekend for brunch. It was our first time at the restaurant and we absolutely loved it - the space and the food is amazing. The restaurant itself reminded us of a bistro you would see on the corner of a street in downtown Paris. The brunch menu was excellent - difficultly selecting among many desirable menu items is a great problem to have for sure. We also really enjoyed the service - the food came out fresh and quickly and our server, who's name was Elliot I believe, was very friendly. We really enjoyed our visit and are excited to go back sometime soon. The only thing I would say that we did not like was that the price for their food, especially breakfast food, was very high comparatively and many of their entrees did not come with sides so you have to pay and order for those separately. Aside from an above average price, their food and service were great.
Good, but very greasy. Nice service!
This is an amazing eatery. Amazing people work here.  Their falafel is fresh and very yummy. We had their plate me and pocket, both of them the spicy version. It was very good.
This is the absolute best food in Bethesda. The food is great. The service is amazing. I will keep coming back.
A must-go gem in Bethesda! Duck duck goose is chic and simply delicious. The honey roasted duck is a must try!

Great service! Went out for brunch and everything went well, almost forgot for a second that this pandemic is happening. All the guidelines are followed correctly. Service was great! Good was delicious! We have been coming here since they opened five years ago. Chef Alfred has trained his chefs well and I wish him continued success in Baltimore and Bethesda!

I asked for medium, it came out dripping with blood.  I didn't have the heart to head back to return it since I did carry out, but I got halfway through it before giving up the battle. Had I ordered a burger tar tar, it would have been amazing! But yeah, tread lightly when you order something other than well done.  They get a few stars for the good fries though.  Probably not heading back for a few years. My gory burger has me shook.

Went for a birthday and the hostess recognized that they'd be doing something special. That was the highlight of the meal. Server was not kind, very to the point. Regular and brunch menu were very similar, but was announced that nothing from regular menu would be available. That's what the birthday person had wanted so the brisk waiter shut that down promptly. Guest were told no sides came with steak sandwich so they ordered the potatoes and the steak did in fact come with potatoes so we had way to much. As the meal ended there was no mention of the birthday so the person celebrating went home disappointed. Would not recommend.

This place is incredible! They have an excellent take on a classic French brasserie. Their menu is quiet creative, focusing on seasonal ingredients, flavors, and dishes with modern twist to them. I tried their lunch portion of their grilled chicken sandwich and calms & mussel accompanied with chorizo and white wine. Enjoyed every bite of both dishes. Their staff are friendly, attentive, and accommodating and renders great service.
service staff was wonderful, food even better.. highly recommend the dry aged duck, their moscow mule was also spot on 😊

Met friends here for dinner on a Saturday night. Staff were friendly and attentive. There are a good selection of cocktails, well made. A decent wine list, but can't speak to beers as didn't order any. Small plates to start were creative and delicious. I enjoyed the duck sausage. Mains were also well prepared with seasonal purees and sauces decorating the plates. I had the duck breast which arrived just as I ordered it, medium-rare. Tried fries from a friend - crisp and well seasoned. He didn't like the burger however, but that is partially his fault for ordering it well done, it came out dry but what do you expect with ground chuck. Desserts were well made and delicious. Overall a good experience. Not a place for the price conscious person.

If you go.. you must order the Duck Duck Burger..Hands down the best burger I ever ate. I will definitely go back for that burger! P.s. we ask the burger to be split to 4 to share but you will want the whole burger to yourself!

Everything about Duck Duck Goose was amazing. For the mains we had the duck duck burger, which the combination of cherry marmalade and brie was delicious,  and the braised lamb shank which was our overall winner. We will definitely be back for more.

This was a good dining experience in a comfortable and warm environment.  The space is small yet intimate but doesn't feel crowded or overbearing.  Sat outside on a warm evening and it made for a pleasant setting.  The wines were mostly French and one might expect but offered a good variety at differing price points.  The small plates were excellent as was the main course.  I had the salmon which was prepared wonderfully.  I would recommend this to anyone looking for a quaint and friendly destination.

I had a lovely evening here with a group of 10. The wait staff were all so great. They were polite but not in an overly fancy way that makes you feel like some kind of royalty from the 1800s. It was just perfect and one of the best wait staffs I've ever experienced. I felt respected but they were also fun and not cookie cutter humans: the restaurant allowed them to be themselves with style of clothing, piercing and exposure of tattoos.  Now for the food and drink. I got some kind of daily special cocktail that I don't remember the name of, but it was a deliciously perfect mix. For my meal I had the scallops with Israeli couscous and it was fantastic. The Israeli couscous is larger and smoother which was a perfect fit for this dish instead of regular couscous. The scallops were cooked well, and the puree and sparing use of green apple was a great blend. It was surprising but tasted like it all belonged together. Really complimentary flavors and I would absolutely get this again. I could not stop eating this dish!

Had lunch here the other day with my girlfriend. The weather was nice so we dined outside. The food was unsurprisingly (anything by Chef Ashish Alfred usually is beyond 5 star gourmet deliciousness) delicious. Who would think about Cauliflower soup and Cauliflower sandwich seriously delicious and healthy. My new favorite spot for good eats. Looking forward to dining at the Baltimore location soon also. Keep up the amazing work.

Excellent upscale French food.

I would have preferred 3.5 stars. I had the dry aged duck, and for it being what could be assumed as the signature dish, it wasn't amazing. As a bit of a duck fan, it did not have a flavor, tenderness, or texture consistent with the idea that dry aged normally conveys. We also had the halibut special. For being a special, it was just fish. We shared the pappardelle and duck pasta, and it lacked seasoning. I also found the pasta tough, most likely overworked in the dough phase.  However, the steak tartar was great. We also had the smoked scallop ceviche and it was also very nice. The smoke is more of an aroma than a flavor.  The staff was very nice and friendly. We were the first table of the evening, and everyone at one point helped serve us in some form.  I recommend having a reservation, as even though we started as the only guests, they were very concerned about us not having a reservation. They also limit you to 2 hours at your table.
Top notch food. I ate at a table outside. Lamb Bolognese, and Duck. It was all excellent.

What a wonderful place we've discovered yesterday! FOOD: very interesting, creative and delicious. The only thing that could be improved it's the portion size verses pricing (particularly in entrees where amounts of garnishes dis-proportionally small in the ratio to protein part of the dish). SERVICE: was very nice, efficient and professional AMBIANCE: cozy, comfortable, but a bit too loud when a full house for keeping a conversation. VALUE: a bit higher then it should be considering the portion sizes, but because of the quality of the food probably not high enough to scare customers away. CONCLUSION: when in Bethesda worth coming back.
Haven't had a meal that good in a while.

Not even sure where to start. I am typically not the one to complain at all. I can take a lot, but this time, I had to write a review. Our reservation was at 8 PM and our table was running a little behind, which is fine, no big deal. The bar is so small that we could not even squeeze in to grab a drink because people were already on top of each other so we decided to wait for our table instead. I used to work as a waitress for 8 years and between sideworks and taking care of my clients I know what being busy means, but this time, our waiter had zero sense of time or attention. He came in to our table, nice and polite, maybe a little too excited but still, friendly and amicable. He introduced himself and he was never to be seen until dessert time. I had to physically grab another waitress who was standing at the bar to take our order after we already received our 1st round of drinks and that was 40 min later. Our original waiter came back to check on us and he was sweating bullets. We saw him talk to the chef in the kitchen the whole time and I am guessing it was so hot out there that when he came out on the floor he was drenched, very unappealing for a waiter who is going to take care of your food and drinks. He said he was going to change our silverware but never did. And he vanished again. I then grabbed another waitress to get our dessert order because no one checked on us. Meanwhile, we were watching the staff, including our waiter, taking selfies between the bar and the kitchen. At that point, we could have just left, but it was my friends birthday so I really wanted her to get some dessert, at least. The food was not that great. She had the risotto and it was way too salty, so she returned it and I shared my crab salad with her instead. We did not want to wait another 40 min to get our food. Dessert came, and our waiter finally appeared after I waived at him. He offered a dessert on the house because of the food, which was kind of him to do but nevertheless, he was not around when we needed him. the dessert came, and honestly, it was not worth it at all. The profiteroles were good! but the other one was too dry. It could use more cream or sauce. The mille feuilles was too much and too dry. Anyways, I would not go back to that place. It's nice and cozy but not worth my time and money. Pour mes compatriotes Francais, je ne recommande pas de manger dans ce restaurant. La qualitee alimentaire n'est pas de hauteur et le service, ben n'en parlons surtout pas. Bonne chance a vous si vous decider d'y mettre les pieds. Peut etre le bar lui meme serait le mieux sinon.
lamb bolognese was decent, cauliflower steak was bold, mushroom risotto was more like wine risotto, and the mussels were passable.

Delicious meal! Fantastic service! Every course was a wonder. The location and outdoor seating feels very Parisian. I will definitely be back. Highly recommend getting a bottle of wine with dinner and lingering over the food - half the fun of our dinner was people watching.

Great environment. Pleasant staff. They made us delectable non-alcoholic cocktails upon request. The charred broccolinis were delicious and very unique. The main course others were okay. The Jenny could use a couple of vegetarian choices for the main course.
Overpriced and unhappy with the service I received. They declinded my valid out-of-state license in front of my colleagues.

Service was great..food was delicious. Definitely an experience.
The food and drinks were simply phenomenal! Easy to see how it was voted one of the best restaurants in Maryland.

Nice little bistro, good food, friendly and engaging staff.  We started with bread with a  garlic-onion-ramp butter, which was very tasty.  S had a cheese plate with brie and manchego, with a little array of accompaniments.  S says the plate was better than most, but admitted most of the sides were not things she'd eat.  I had a cucumber crab salad which was great..  The cucumber and seasoning was light and added to rather than masked the crab.  I also had a aged duck breast, which was also great.  Dessert was a somewhat unremarkable puff pastry dish, but the caramel chocolate sauce was good.  Overall a very nice experience (especially the staff).  Downsides were the price and it's small enough that just one table made the whole place loud.

And all 3 stars are for food and service because the venue is just terrible!  If my chair got smacked one more time by the lady behind me a fight might have broken out.  The waitress saw this and gave us a drink and apology for the EXTREMELY cramped quarters.  Interesting menu, good food but NOT WORTH THE BS of having people sitting on your lap while you eat.
One word.. AMAZING! Love the food from start to finish. You have to see it to believe it, come and ck out to food everything was amazing 🤗
This place is amazing. The cocktsils are great and the food is delicious. Thetables fill up fast, but a full menu is available at the bar as well
Had a great time! Superb wine selection and cocktails. I hope to be back soon!

Chef and Owner of Duck Duck Goose takes familiar dishes and takes it up a couple of notches! Steak Tenderloin Tartare, Cauliflower Steak, Mushroom Risotto, Veal Wellington with Seared Foie Gras and Dry Aged Medium Rare Duck. Cocktail drink was Golden Goose (with gold leaves!). Amazing, amazing, amazing. Our server Isabela was the best! A true Bethesda gem.

They will not let you order duck breast more than medium done, my mother-in-law got the waiter to let her order a medium against his stern recommendation,  when she got it she sent it back for another searing.  My medium was a red medium, I really wish I had medium well.
Great experience! The food was amazing and the staff worked as a team and was very attentive.  We are definitely dining at Duck Duck Goose again!!! Thank you for a wonderful experience!

Started out great with great food and a beautiful atmosphere. Then, they packed in as many tables as possible so you can hear your fellow diners think. On our last couple visits (we gave them the benefit of the doubt), the food was overcooked and the menu selections became increasingly limited. The chef was there -- can't blame it on just the staff. Too bad.  It didn't take long to go from "great" to "below-average".

Lovely place with great food and excellent cocktails.  Even before ordering the kitchen sent out a small amuse bouche.  That's my kind of place.  The Duck L'Orange cocktail with a duck bacon chaser is genius.  Our tabled shared the Beef Tartare, Scallops Ceviche, and Squid Ink Spaghetti apps - all very tasty.  I had the Quail entree.  A bit on the small side for someone with an appetite, but it was cooked well.  My friends had the Tournedos and had no complaints.  The only downside could be that there isn't much of a dessert selection.  The staff is awesome!
Wonderful food and terrific ambiance. Staff was very attentive... Another great experience at Duck Duck Goose.

Excellent lunch prices. The bread was unbelievably fresh; delicious overall, quite happy

Didn’t get a good experience. Pretentious atmosphere and dishes with ridiculously expansive prices, but very average taste. We came for the halibut dish. But they were out if it. In fact, from six or so entrees, they were out of two.. You need a magnify glass to find a mash potato, which was a part of my dish. Scallops for 28$ was a plate of probably 3 large scallops, which were cut on several pieces and arrange in circle on the plate, with a few broccolino (?) (a fancy for the broccoli) pieces . And on the empty middle of plate, the parsley sauce was poured… Even I do not need much food, I was absolutely hungry after that meal and got some chicken from my friend’s plate ($24, but was tasty enough with a good size). The waiter absolutely didn’t care that my friend barely touched her fish dish. He just asked “are you done” and took the plate. Cheese plate - $18 for 3 small pieces of cheese with one cherry tomato, one strip of the marinated mushroom and a slice of marinated onion…. In short, 4 least expensive entrees, with a tiny cheese plate, and two glasses of white wine cost us $168 (without tips). So, after a $200 dinner, we being still hungry went to the Italian place nearby and enjoy a tasty, but not pretentious food for the fraction of costs. With so many nice places around, it was a huge mistake to come there (strong wind and sudden cold weather stopped us for going somewhere else after we sat down)
Amazing food - out of this world! If you're looking for a unique, delicious and fun place to dine, this place is it!! Best food in town!

Awesome venue all around. Chef Alfred had a great team in place here and the food is consistently amazing. The drinks are also quite good and it's worth trying a unique cocktail even if that is not your usual MO. The duck, the burger, the halibut, the beef tartare, and the napoleon for dessert are among my family's favorites. We also had the cauliflower steak this last time and it was incredibly good. You really can't go wrong. Do yourself a favor and go here when you can.
